{
  "_doc": [
    "Declarative task list for prod data injection. Each key is a task ID;",
    "each value is an ORDERED list of shell commands to run inside the",
    "wot-ingest Cloud Run Job (i.e. inside the wot-api container against",
    "prod Cloud SQL via DATABASE_URL secret).",
    "",
    "Invariants enforced by scripts/check_manifest_integrity.py (CI):",
    "  1. Every command is a non-empty string.",
    "  2. Every 'python scripts/X.py' references a file that exists in repo.",
    "  3. Tasks must be idempotent. Re-running must not duplicate or",
    "     overwrite existing data. apply_descriptions() is NULL-only;",
    "     structural ingesters use INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING.",
    "  4. Within a task, ORDER scripts so any auto-downloading variant runs",
    "     FIRST (it populates data/<file>); file-based variants run AFTER",
    "     and reuse the downloaded file. Some systems still need data files",
    "     baked into the Docker image (data/* is .gitignored today). See",
    "     docs/handover/runbooks/ingest-prod.md 'Data file dependencies'.",
    "",
    "Usage from a developer laptop after a backfill PR merges:",
    "  ./scripts/ingest-prod.sh anzsic_2006 soc_2018 mesh",
    "",
    "Add a new task: append a key here, run the integrity check, ship.",
    "See docs/handover/runbooks/ingest-prod.md for full runbook."
  ],

